
@startuml
' Class Diagram for De Lijn's MENSO System

class Bus {
  +id: String
  +lineNumber: String
  +currentTrajectory: Trajectory
}

class Line {
  +id: String
  +lineNumber: String
  +name: String
  +trajectories: Set<Trajectory>
}

class Trajectory {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +status: Status
  +approvalHistory: List<Approval>
  +startDate: Date
  +endDate: Date
}

enum Status {
  ACTIVE
  SUSPENDED
  CANCELLED
}

class Approval {
  +id: String
  +date: Date
  +decision: Decision
  +notes: String
}

enum Decision {
  APPROVED
  REJECTED
  MODIFIED
}

class User {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +homeAddress: String
  +officeAddress: String
  +workingHours: String
  +mensoCard: MensoCard
}

class MensoCard {
  +id: String
  +userId: String
  +trips: List<Trip>
}

class Trip {
  +id: String
  +date: Date
  +time: Time
  +lineId: String
  +categoryId: String
}

class Category {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +pricePerKm: Double
}

class Invoice {
  +id: String
  +userId: String
  +month: Month
  +totalAmount: Double
  +discount: Double
  +trips: List<Trip>
}

class Payment {
  +id: String
  +invoiceId: String
  +amountPaid: Double
  +paymentDate: Date
}

' Relationships

Bus --> Line : belongs to
Line --> Trajectory : contains
Trajectory --> Approval : has
Trajectory --> Status : has status
User --> MensoCard : owns
MensoCard --> Trip : records
Trip --> Line : belongs to
Trip --> Category : relates to
User --> Invoice : receives
Invoice --> Trip : includes
Invoice --> Payment : may have
@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Classes and Relationships:

- **`Bus`**: Each bus is associated with a `Line`.
- **`Line`**: Groups multiple `Trajectory` objects, which can be overlapping or variant.
- **`Trajectory`**: Represents a specific route. It has an approval history and a status (active, suspended, cancelled).
- **`Status`**: An enumerated type indicating the current status of a trajectory.
- **`Approval`**: Tracks the approval process by authorities. Can be approved, rejected, or modified.
- **`User`**: A user who subscribes to the MENSO card and provides personal data.
- **`MensoCard`**: Contains trip records for a user.
- **`Trip`**: Records the date, time, line, and category of each trip made using the MENSO card.
- **`Category`**: Defines pricing rules based on the line category.
- **`Invoice`**: Generated monthly, based on trips and discounts.
- **`Payment`**: Represents a payment made by the user for an invoice.

